g-firefox-anthropic-red-team/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://blog.mozilla.org/en/firefox/hardening-firefox-anthro...\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.wsj.com/tech/ai/send-us-more-anthropics-claude-sniffs-out-bevy-of-bugs-c6822075\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003ehttps://www.wsj.com/tech/ai/send-us-more-anthropics-claude-s...\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273854\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273854\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 443\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 129\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://www.anthropic.com/news/mozilla-firefox-security","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273854","date_published":"2026-03-06T11:53:18Z","author":{"name":"todsacerdoti","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=todsacerdoti"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273070","title":"How Much Money Jeff Bezos Made Since You Started Reading This Page","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://bezoscalculator.com/\"\u003ehttps://bezoscalculator.com/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273070\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273070\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 105\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 133\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://bezoscalculator.com/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47273070","date_published":"2026-03-06T10:06:06Z","author":{"name":"TigerUniversity","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=TigerUniversity"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272799","title":"LibreSprite – open-source pixel art editor","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://libresprite.github.io/\"\u003ehttps://libresprite.github.io/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272799\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272799\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 246\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 79\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://libresprite.github.io/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272799","date_published":"2026-03-06T09:22:00Z","author":{"name":"nicoloren","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=nicoloren"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272734","title":"We might all be AI engineers now","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://yasint.dev/we-might-all-be-ai-engineers-now/\"\u003ehttps://yasint.dev/we-might-all-be-ai-engineers-now/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272734\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272734\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 159\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 246\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://yasint.dev/we-might-all-be-ai-engineers-now/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272734","date_published":"2026-03-06T09:13:30Z","author":{"name":"sn0wflak3s","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=sn0wflak3s"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272338","title":"It took four years until 2011’s iOS 5 gave everyone an emoji keyboard","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://unsung.aresluna.org/im-obviously-taking-a-risk-here-by-advertising-emoji-directly/\"\u003ehttps://unsung.aresluna.org/im-obviously-taking-a-risk-here-by-advertising-emoji-directly/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272338\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272338\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 123\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 78\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://unsung.aresluna.org/im-obviously-taking-a-risk-here-by-advertising-emoji-directly/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47272338","date_published":"2026-03-06T08:13:28Z","author":{"name":"tobr","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=tobr"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270807","title":"Show HN: Swarm – Program a colony of 200 ants using a custom assembly language","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eWe built an ant colony simulation as an internal hiring challenge at Moment and decided to open it up publicly.\u003cp\u003eYou write a program in a custom assembly-like (we call it ant-ssembly) instruction set that controls 200 ants. Each ant can sense nearby cells (food, pheromones, home, other ants) but has no global view. The only coordination mechanism is pheromone trails, which ants can emit and sense them, but that's it. Your program runs identically on every ant.\u003cp\u003eThe goal is to collect the highest percentage of food across a set of maps. Different map layouts (clustered food, scattered, obstacles) reward very different strategies. The leaderboard is live.\u003cp\u003eGrand prize is a trip to Maui for two paid for by Moment. Challenge closes March 12.\u003cp\u003eCurious what strategies people discover. We've seen some surprisingly clever emergent behavior internally.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270807\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270807\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 178\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 60\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://dev.moment.com/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270807","date_published":"2026-03-06T04:15:40Z","author":{"name":"armandhammer10","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=armandhammer10"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270784","title":"System76 on Age Verification Laws","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://blog.system76.com/post/system76-on-age-verification/\"\u003ehttps://blog.system76.com/post/system76-on-age-verification/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270784\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270784\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 798\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 559\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://blog.system76.com/post/system76-on-age-verification/","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47270784","date_published":"2026-03-06T04:12:26Z","author":{"name":"LorenDB","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=LorenDB"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47269263","title":"Where things stand with the Department of War","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/news/where-stand-department-war\"\u003ehttps://www.anthropic.com/news/where-stand-department-war\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47269263\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47269263\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 606\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 749\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://www.anthropic.com/news/where-stand-department-war","external_url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47269263","date_published":"2026-03-06T00:40:41Z","author":{"name":"surprisetalk","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=surprisetalk"}},{"id":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47268662","title":"The next generations of Bubble Tea, Lip Gloss, and Bubbles are available now","content_html":"\n\u003cp\u003eArticle URL: \u003ca href=\"https://charm.land/blog/v2/\"\u003ehttps://charm.land/blog/v2/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComments URL: \u003ca href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47268662\"\u003ehttps://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47268662\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePoints: 198\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e# Comments: 84\u003c/p\u003e\n","url":"https://charm.land